column2: Real time bidding.In general there are two task in real time bidding.First is a task of optimizing requests choice
column3: second is a optimizing bid prices.A first task answers on a question
column5: to get a revenue.The revenue is get from the target events: Clicks
column6: Conversions …So we may make a model that predict the events. It’s a classification task and may be solve as usual classification problem of binary classification.A second task answers on a question
column8: to get a more benefit and win an auction .I consider the second task.The second is more complex
column9: need increase number of win bids. Because only a wining bid gives revenue.The trivial solution is to set a bid price little smaller then an expected benefit
column10: for example smaller by 10 % . But this solution is not optimal when there is a limit of our budget
column11: and limits our benefit with 10%.Not bad solution is predict a probability of win and if the probability smaller then a given value increase a bid price. It’s a classification task too.But there is another way. Lets try to find an optimal price of the bid that layers between the loss price and win price
column12: said for the same requests. And then if the win probability for this bid price smaller then some value
column13: we increase the bid price.At first glance
column14: this is a regression problem. But there is one problem. We only know the cost of losing when we lose the auction
column15: but we don't know the next win price. In another case
column16: we know the winning price when we won the auction
column17: but we do not know the price of the next loss.And in general the bid price is a function of an input request. That is a set of categorical and numerical values.Such as : exchange id

column23: and so on.Our model need to predict an optimal price for each request.My approach is to use a custom loss function that solves the problem. (I called loss YuLoss.)The loss function is based with MSE loss with little changes
column24: or may base with any other regression loss.The main idea is :If the prediction price less or equivale then the loss price we penalty our model.If the prediction price more then the loss price we don’t penalty our model with MSE loss.If the prediction price less or equavile then the win price we don’t penalty our model.If the prediction price more then the win price we penalty our model with MSE loss.MSE (target

column8: в то время как ChatGPT разработан для ответа на разнообразные вопросы и задачи
column9: включая общение с людьми на естественном языке.Кроме того

column14: чтобы предлагать более точные предложения и подсказки для написания нового кода.В целом
column16: ускоряя процесс написания кода и помогая избежать ошибок

column11: мы с семьей живем в Санкт-Петербурге. Уже здесь увлекся яхтингом. Вначале это были небольшие прогулки под парусом

column8: from simple calculations to complex data analysis.Some of the most commonly used functions include:Math.round(): rounds a number to the nearest integerMath.random(): generates a random number between 0 and 1Math.max(): returns the highest value in a set of numbersMath.min(): returns the lowest value in a set of numbersMath.abs(): returns the absolute value of a numberMath.pow(): raises a number to a specified powerMath.sqrt(): returns the square root of a numberMath.sin(): returns the sine of an angleBy using these functions
